Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into
2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Trim the @Aubergine{2}(trimmed and sliced into rounds approximately 1cm thick),
then slice into rounds approximately 1cm thick. Pop the rounds onto a #baking
tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer (use two baking trays if necessary).

When the oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf until soft and
golden, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the potato chunks onto another #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out
in a single layer (use two baking trays if necessary).

Roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While everything roasts, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}).

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Once hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%grams} and fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}. Next, add in the garlic and stir-fry, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Harissa Paste{50%grams}(add less if you'd prefer things milder),
@Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{50%milliliters} for the sauce (see pantry for both
amounts).

Bring the sauce to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Stir the @Butter{20%grams} through the sauce until melted.

== Assembly ==

Spoon half of the tomato sauce into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and
spread out in an even layer. Lay half of the roasted aubergine rounds on top,
then sprinkle over half of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%grams}.

Repeat this once more with the remaining sauce, aubergine and cheese -
parmigiana made!

== Baking ==

When the potatoes have about 10 mins left, bake the parmigiana on the top shelf
of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{8-10%minutes}.

When your parmigiana is ready, allow to stand for a couple mins before serving.

Share between your plates with the roast potatoes and
@Wild Rocket{20%grams}(leaves separated) alongside.

Drizzle the @Balsamic Glaze{12%milliliters} over the leaves to finish.

Enjoy!